channel.description:
[b]Description:[/b] How to create a new/custom skill for a 317 PI Server and Client
[b]Difficulty:[/b] 8/10 (if you don't know how to code a working skill)
[b]Assumed Knowledge[/b]: How to use CTRL+F button to search, Copy & Paste and how to code a skill.

[b]Tested Server:[/b] My Project Insanity 317. Note: May not work on all servers.
[b]Files/Classes Modified:[/b] Server Side: Client.java, SkillGuides.java, Config.java, PlayerAssistant.java, Client Side: Skills.java

[hr]

[b]Step 1:[/b] First off, we are going to go into our Client files and search for Skills.java. Open it up and search for [code]"-unused-",[/code]
There should be 3 unused skills. Replace one with the name of your skill. For example, i will be making a Possess skill. so i changed mine to [code]"-Possessing-",[/code]
Save.

[b]Step 2:[/b] Go into your Server files and search for Client.java. Open it up and search for [code]	private Runecrafting runecrafting = new Runecrafting(this);[/code]
Under it add this [code]	private Possessing possessing = new Possessing(this);[/code]
Now search for [code]public void process() {[/code] Your server should have it. Now under it add [code]getPA().sendFrame126("@gre@Possessing level: " + playerLevel[21] + ".", 7341);[/code]
This means that when you click your quest bar, It will show what level your custom skill is.
Now search for [code]	public Runecrafting getRunecrafting() {
		return runecrafting;
	}[/code]
Under that add [code]	public Possessing getPossessing() {
		return possessing;
	}[/code]

Save.

[b]Step 3:[/b] Open up SkillGuides.java and search for [code]	public static void rcInterface(Client client) {
		skillsInterface(client, "Runecrafting", 
					6422, 1, "Air runes",
					6436, 2, "Mind runes", 
					6438, 20, "Body runes", 
					6430, 35, "Chaos runes",  
					561, 44, "Nature runes", 
					6434, 54, "Law runes", 
					6432, 65, "Death runes", 
					565, 77, "Blood runes");
	}[/code]

Under it add your own thing that suites your custom skill. I Added [code]	public static void possessInterface(Client client) {
		skillsInterface(client, "Possessing", 
					3241, 1, "Man", 
					3243, 10, "Farmer", 
					3245, 25, "Warrior", 
					3249, 40, "Guard", 
					3251, 53, "Knights of ardogne", 
					3255, 70, "Paladin",
					3257, 75, "Gnome",
					3259, 80, "Hero");
	}[/code]

This means that at level 1, i can possess men. The number 3241 is the man id.
You can find out NPC ids and/or Item Ids yourself at www.google.com :)

[b]Step 4:[/b] go into config.java and search for [code]	public static final int RUNECRAFTING_EXPERIENCE = 40;[/code]
Under that add [code]	public static final int POSSESSING_EXPERIENCE = 40;[/code]

[b]Step 5:[/b] Search for PlayerAssistant.java and inside that look for [code]            case 20:
			sendFrame126("Congratulations, you just advanced a runecrafting level!", 4268);
			sendFrame126("Your runecrafting level is now "+getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[skill])+".", 4269);
			c.sendMessage("Congratulations, you just advanced a runecrafting level.");
			c.magePoints += 20;
			sendFrame164(4267);
            break;[/code]

Under that add something like that and change it that it suites your needs. For example I added [code]            case 21:
			sendFrame126("Congratulations, you just advanced a Possessing level!", 4270);
			sendFrame126("Your Possessing level is now "+getLevelForXP(c.playerXP[skill])+".", 4271);
			c.sendMessage("Congratulations, you just advanced a Possessing level.");
			c.magePoints += 20;
			sendFrame164(4269);
		}[/code]

[b]Step 6:[/b] Note:[i]This is the really really really hard part for beginners. I haven't completed this myself yet.[/i]
Go into your Server files and go into Src >> Server >> Model >> Players >> Skills
Now you must code your own skill for your self. (To test that this works I copied the thieving skill and renamed it)

[b]Step 7:[/b] Now that you have coded your skill. Compile everything and log on to your server.
Go on the quest tab and you shall see that is says: 
[img]http://i931.photobucket.com/albums/ad154/pzezima2/PossessingLevel.png[/img]


